{
  "stem": "22237.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I remember getting-- I was depressed about that, because not so much the grownups threw the books [LAUGHS] in the fire, but the children.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I even recognized some of them from playing, from not so much school, because I went to a Jewish school, but you learned to-- you-- you-- you recognize people.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You recognize children, especially.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that was the first thing that depressed me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then of course these banners, when you walked into the public places that I mentioned before, was hard to take.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then, in time, people-- you heard about things-- people were intimidated, a cousin was-- was rolled into some water, and he had to get out of the water.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He had a hard time, and he just about made it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That was already back in 1933.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then as-- as the years went by, like in 1934, there was a terrible paper being published.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was called the [NON-ENGLISH], Stormtrooper newspaper.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Everything seemed to be stormtroopers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Troopers.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And that was a horrible paper.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "That affected me terribly, because it was-- it-- it had all-- it-- it was plastered on all these stores that sold newspapers.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And in the morning, going to school, I would see these [NON-ENGLISH], and people standing and reading them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And what did they list in the [NON-ENGLISH]?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They-- they had people-- faces with long noses and saliva running from their mouth and looking at-- of course, typically, you know, it meant Jewish people. 'Cuz there were-- they always talk-- they always wrote about Jewish people with their long noses.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they were looking at little Gentile children, greedily looking at the money that the children had in their hands, like they wanted to steal the money from these children.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
